== COMMENTS

Alzheimer's is quite a common disease with no cure. However, treatment in the early stages can really help to delay the development of symptoms. The current methods of diagnosis could be drastically improved and the development of this machine learning model is a step in that direction. It's really cool to think that this might have a large impact on people's lives for the better.
